import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['price'])
    
    ax = plt.gca()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the trend of S&P 500 stock prices over time?")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.hist(data['price'], bins=20)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of S&P 500 stock prices?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data['daily_return'] = data['price'].pct_change()
    data['daily_return'].fillna(0, inplace=True)
    average_daily_return = data['daily_return'].mean()
    
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['daily_return'])
    plt.axhline(average_daily_return, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Daily Return: {average_daily_return:.2f}')
    
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Daily Return')
    plt.title('What is the average daily return of S&P 500 stock prices?')
    plt.legend()
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['date'], data['price'], c=data['price'], cmap='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between S&P 500 stock prices and the overall market?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
